- `DESIGN.md` complete, no skeleton comments left.
- `tasks.yaml` has real `modules:` (Phase 0 + implementation), every task with a unit test,
  every module with a gate, a clean dependency order, and consistent worker assignment.
- `code/raster.yaml` `description:` holds the generated one-line build description (no longer the
  `(to be generated during raster plan)` placeholder).
- `PROGRESS.md` lists every gate and task.
- the user has signed off. Then the project is ready for **`raster queue`** — which submits the
  build chain to trundlr (running `raster build` per task and `raster test` per gate). Tell the
